.TH "drm_legacy_irq_by_busid" 9 "drm_legacy_irq_by_busid" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_legacy_irq_by_busid \- Get interrupt from bus ID
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_legacy_irq_by_busid
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ","
.BI "struct drm_file *file_priv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "data" 12
IOCTL parameter pointing to a drm_irq_busid structure
.IP "file_priv" 12
DRM file private.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Finds the PCI device with the specified bus id and gets its IRQ number.
This IOCTL is deprecated, and will now return EINVAL for any busid not equal
to that of the device that this DRM instance attached to.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or a negative error code on failure.
